35:16.197 --> 35:17.031
Where are you?

35:17.115 --> 35:19.492
-[Raymond] <i>Elizabeth, we need to leave.</i>
-Wait. No.

35:19.575 --> 35:21.702
Answer me. Who became Reddington?

35:21.786 --> 35:24.455
-[Raymond] <i>Elizabeth, we have to go.</i>
-Who is he?

35:24.539 --> 35:26.916
-[Dembe] <i>Townsend's here!</i>
-[gunshots]

35:26.999 --> 35:28.918
-[Raymond] <i>We have to go.</i>
-No! I need more!

35:29.001 --> 35:32.463
Who took his identity? Who? There's more!

35:32.547 --> 35:35.424
[Raymond] <i>There's no more if you're dead.</i>

35:35.508 --> 35:36.509
[gunshot]

35:39.637 --> 35:41.639
[suspenseful music playing]

35:47.103 --> 35:48.896
Dembe, we need to get to the nest.

35:54.861 --> 35:56.237
We're almost there.

36:04.537 --> 36:05.872
She needs a doctor.

36:11.836 --> 36:13.588
[Townsend] You know
what she needs even more?

36:15.006 --> 36:16.090
A mortician.

36:20.469 --> 36:22.013
[ominous music playing]

36:22.096 --> 36:23.181
It's ironic.

36:23.264 --> 36:26.684
You devoted your life to protecting her,
and in the end she betrays you.

36:26.767 --> 36:28.936
Relax. That's it. Keep breathing.

36:29.020 --> 36:32.356
You wanted to use
the tracking chip to find me?

36:32.440 --> 36:35.026
She made it possible
for me to use it to find you.

36:35.109 --> 36:36.777
Elizabeth, stay with me.

36:36.861 --> 36:39.655
-Keep breathing.
-By the way, where are we?

36:39.739 --> 36:42.116
A nest in Latvia.

36:42.200 --> 36:44.410
-Even for you, this is a tad dramatic.
-[Raymond] Stay with me.

36:44.493 --> 36:45.953
She and I made a deal.

36:46.037 --> 36:49.081
She would lead me to you,
and in exchange I would let her live.

36:49.165 --> 36:52.877
Unfortunately for her,
deals are made to be broken.

36:52.960 --> 36:54.086
[cell phone rings]

36:54.962 --> 36:55.796
Talk to me.

36:55.880 --> 36:58.841
Radley says you're on-site.
Am I clear to send the extraction team?

36:58.925 --> 37:00.134
Clear as ice.

37:00.218 --> 37:01.510
On its way, sir.

37:01.594 --> 37:02.428
And, sir...

37:03.804 --> 37:05.181
congratulations.

37:07.433 --> 37:09.644
Killing her won't bring your family back.

37:09.727 --> 37:11.646
I always wondered how you gathered

37:11.729 --> 37:14.815
such an enormous amount
of intelligence all these years.

37:14.899 --> 37:18.194
-This is quite the operation you've built.
-It's yours if you help her.

37:19.779 --> 37:20.947
No, no, no.

37:21.030 --> 37:21.948
It's all right.

37:22.615 --> 37:26.327
Of course, it's nothing
compared to your commitment.

37:26.410 --> 37:29.580
The decision to live
as Raymond Reddington.

37:29.664 --> 37:32.625
To give up your life
to live as someone else.

37:32.708 --> 37:36.045
I can't imagine
loving anyone enough to do that.

37:36.128 --> 37:38.631
I have other facilities.
You can have all of it.

37:38.714 --> 37:42.635
I haven't slept through the night
in 25 years.

37:42.718 --> 37:44.929
Tonight I'll sleep like a baby.

37:45.012 --> 37:47.765
-I'll give you whatever you want.
-Whatever I want?

37:47.848 --> 37:49.058
[Raymond] If you help her, yes.

37:49.141 --> 37:50.101
Anything you want.

37:50.768 --> 37:52.561
All I want is for you to watch her die.

38:03.072 --> 38:04.240
[Dembe] Hurry, Raymond!

38:05.616 --> 38:07.285
Help her get down the hatch.

38:22.425 --> 38:23.259
Okay.

38:24.176 --> 38:28.848
There's a first aid kit in the cabinet
and a bottle of vodka in the freezer.

38:29.849 --> 38:35.104
We'll get you properly sloshed
before we go poking around in that wound.

38:37.356 --> 38:39.233
-Is there another way out?
-[Dembe] No.

38:39.317 --> 38:41.319
The hatch is the only way.

38:41.402 --> 38:42.820
[metal banging]

38:42.903 --> 38:43.904
Here.

38:43.988 --> 38:44.822
Take a sip.

39:01.172 --> 39:03.174
[feedback whines over speakers]

39:09.305 --> 39:12.183
As a rule, I don't live with regret...

39:13.100 --> 39:15.895
<i>but what happened</i>
<i>to your family was a horror.</i>

39:16.520 --> 39:18.647
<i>That should never have happened.</i>

39:18.731 --> 39:21.025
When I first got the Sikorsky Archive,

39:22.026 --> 39:26.697
I was young and careless
with some of the materials

39:26.781 --> 39:32.078
<i>that would eventually put you</i>
<i>and your family in harm's way.</i>

39:32.661 --> 39:35.456
I didn't kill them,
but even inadvertently...

39:37.666 --> 39:39.502
you're right to believe that...

39:41.170 --> 39:44.090
I was ultimately responsible
for their deaths.

39:45.174 --> 39:46.759
I appreciate that.

39:48.010 --> 39:50.388
A deathbed confession
is always very moving.

39:50.471 --> 39:52.973
But it won't commute your sentence.

39:53.057 --> 39:56.102
Oh, you had a bite at that apple.
You won't get another one.

39:56.185 --> 39:57.937
I have Elizabeth to thank for that.

39:58.562 --> 40:02.191
I guess my years of dedication
had some impact after all.

40:02.274 --> 40:03.609
So much for irony.

40:03.692 --> 40:05.736
I've waited years for this.

40:05.820 --> 40:10.658
I can wait a few minutes to break through
some flimsy hatch in the floor.

40:11.283 --> 40:15.955
I should tell you that the intelligence
packets weren't the only things

40:16.038 --> 40:18.249
I acquired from my Eastern friend.

40:18.332 --> 40:21.419
<i>As I mentioned, I was young,</i>

40:21.502 --> 40:24.505
and whatever the hell vim is,
I was full of it.

40:24.588 --> 40:26.882
My appetite was voracious.

40:27.800 --> 40:31.053
And as the Soviet Union fell,
I gorged myself

40:31.512 --> 40:33.472
<i>on information,</i>

40:33.556 --> 40:37.017
money, weapons, women, men.

40:37.685 --> 40:40.771
Everyone wanted something,
and I wanted everything,

40:40.855 --> 40:43.023
including a nest in Latvia.

40:43.607 --> 40:44.942
<i>I mean, why not?</i>

40:45.025 --> 40:47.361
<i>Riga's a beautiful city.</i>

40:47.445 --> 40:50.823
The Rundale Palace
puts Versailles to shame.

40:51.824 --> 40:57.538
The country is home to more
than 7,000 breeding pairs of storks,

40:57.621 --> 40:59.748
and, well, it's a nest.

41:01.750 --> 41:04.044
Built at the height of the Cold War.

41:04.128 --> 41:09.175
<i>This facility is capable</i>
<i>of withstanding a 20-megaton blast.</i>

41:10.176 --> 41:12.136
<i>Well, not the entire facility.</i>

41:12.219 --> 41:17.892
<i>Just the... What did you call it?</i>
<i>"Flimsy hatch" in the floor.</i>

41:18.559 --> 41:24.565
Where the Russkies would take cover
in order to repel the ugly Americans.

41:25.357 --> 41:26.650
And here we are.

41:26.734 --> 41:29.487
<i>You're American. You're ugly.</i>

41:29.570 --> 41:31.280
<i>And I'm about to repel you.</i>

41:34.200 --> 41:36.202
[suspenseful music playing]

41:37.077 --> 41:38.871
-How much longer?
-[man] A minute. Maybe less.

41:38.954 --> 41:40.039
[Townsend] Make it less.

41:40.122 --> 41:43.334
<i>You see, the thing</i>
<i>about buying a Soviet nest</i>

41:43.417 --> 41:45.377
<i>is that it comes fully loaded.</i>

41:45.461 --> 41:47.671
With herring, vodka...

41:48.881 --> 41:50.466
and chlorine trifluoride,

41:50.549 --> 41:54.553
which of all the chemical gases
is of course the most flammable.

41:55.346 --> 41:56.347
[whirring]

41:59.725 --> 42:03.270
What are you gonna do?
Destroy all your intel?

42:03.354 --> 42:05.356
The source of your power?

42:06.774 --> 42:09.401
The source of my power is right here.

42:09.485 --> 42:11.612
She won't be destroyed.

42:11.695 --> 42:13.489
Certainly not by the likes of you.

42:16.075 --> 42:17.535
Aw, f...

42:18.619 --> 42:20.704
[explosion]

42:20.788 --> 42:22.790
[closing theme playing]
